3.20	Ghost_chilli	Bhut Jolokia chili pepper	The Bhut (Ghost) Jolokia or Naga King chili , as it is commonly known—also known variously by other names (see etymology section below) in its native region, sometimes Naga Jolokia—is a chili pepper previously recognized by Guinness World Records as the hottest pepper in the world. The pepper is typically called the ghost chili by U.S. media.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f1/Naga-jolokia_edit1.jpg/220px-Naga-jolokia_edit1.jpg
